description: Late Middle English arterie, borrowing from Old French artaire and Latin artēria (“a windpipe; an artery”), from Ancient Greek ᾰ̓ρτηρῐ́ᾱ (artēríā, “windpipe; artery”).

entries.meaning: (anatomy) Any of the muscular- and elastic-walled blood vessels forming part of the circulation system by which blood is conveyed away from the heart regardless of its oxygenation status; see pulmonary artery.
examples: Hyponyms: alloartery, arteriole, endartery, microartery; see also Thesaurus:artery

entries.meaning: (transport) A major transit corridor in a system of roads, rivers, or railway lines.
